{"serial": "84006", "department_serial": 72, "code": "TM7044", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "The mathematical foundation of geometric deep learning", "ch": "幾何深度學習數學基礎"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chen, Chien-Chang"], "ch": ["陳健章"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 2, "session": ["2", "3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "R3", "room": "113"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "生醫科學與工程學系跨領域轉譯醫學博士班", "en": "PhD in Institute of Translational and Interdisciplinary Medicine"}, "system": {"ch": "碩博同修", "en": "Master/Doctoral Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "全部使用", "en": "All"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 41, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "以研習微分幾何以及群論數學理論為方法，來理解現代深度學習網路模型的構造型態、參數前饋與反向的傳遞方法，架構行為過擬合成因，以及張量計算的方法與複雜度分析。期待能以此理論與方法的養成，建立學生輕量型網路最佳化的思考模式，並建構其相關數學理論從而設計具備可解釋性的網路模型。", "en": "Through the mathematical theory of differential geometry and group theory to understand the framework of contemporary modern deep learning network models, the feedforward and reverse transmission of parameters, the causes of overfitting in architectural behavior, and the methods and complexity analysis of tensor calculations. It is expected that with the development of this lecture, students can establish a thinking mechanism for lightweight network optimization and construct relevant mathematical theories to design interpretable network models."}, "outline": {"ch": "1. 深度學習模型的歷史發展與侷限\n2. 幾何深度學習的開端\n3. 高維度資料的歸納偏置、正規化與詛咒\n4. 資料的幾何先驗特性\n5. 對稱性、群表徵以及群不變性\n6. 同構群與自同構群\n7. 變形穩定性\n8. 平移不變性與尺度分離\n10. 圖深度學習網路\n11. 圖卷積深度學習網路\n12. 圖集合\n13. 歐式空間與格點表徵\n14. 群與齊次空間\n15. 測地線與流形\n16. 規範與叢集\n17. 幾何圖與網格表徵\n18. 近代幾何深度學習模型簡介", "en": "1. Historical development and limitations of deep learning models\n2. The beginning of geometric deep learning\n3. Inductive bias, regularization, and curse of high-dimensional data\n4. Characteristics of geometric prior in data\n5. Symmetry, group representation, and group invariance\n6. Isomorphism groups and automorphism groups\n7. Deformation stability\n8. Translation invariance and scale separation\n10. Graph deep learning network\n11. Graph convolution deep learning network\n12. Graph sets\n13. Euclidean space and grid representation\n14. Groups and homogeneous spaces\n15. Geodesics and manifolds\n16. Gauges and Bundles\n17. Geometric graph and mesh representation\n18. Introduction to modern geometric deep learning models"}, "textbook": {"ch": "1.Geometric Deep Learning: Grids, Groups, Graphs, Geodesics, and Gauges, M. M. Bronstein, et. al., 2021.\n2.M. M. Bronstein, et. al., “Geometric Deep Learning: Going beyond Euclidean data,” IEEE Signal Processing Magazine, Vol. 34, July 2017.\n3.F. Monti, et. al., “Geometric Deep Learning on Graphs and Manifolds Using Mixture Model CNNs,” IEEE CVPR, 2017.", "en": "1.Geometric Deep Learning: Grids, Groups, Graphs, Geodesics, and Gauges, M. M. Bronstein, et. al., 2021.\n2.M. M. Bronstein, et. al., “Geometric Deep Learning: Going beyond Euclidean data,” IEEE Signal Processing Magazine, Vol. 34, July 2017.\n3.F. Monti, et. al., “Geometric Deep Learning on Graphs and Manifolds Using Mixture Model CNNs,” IEEE CVPR, 2017."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100", "en": "100"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授", "en": ["Lecture"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "課堂表現    10％\n作業        20％\n課中報告    30％\n學期專題    40％", "en": "Class participation10％\nAssignment    20％\nIn-class presentation30％\nTerm Project40％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "星期四 13點至15點", "en": "Thursday 1pm～3pm"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "18", "en": "18"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "domain": {"ch": "工程科學建模\n\n\n、\n\n\n大數據與機械學習", "en": "工程科學建模\n\n\n、\n\n\n大數據與機械學習"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "轉譯醫學與臨床問題締合", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)"]}, {"competencies": "實驗架構設計與執行", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)"]}, {"competencies": "數據分析、邏輯推演與建模預測", "rating": 